      Description

      The India men's national cricket team represents India in men's international cricket. It is governed by the Board of Control for Cricket in India, and is a Full Member of the International Cricket Council with Test, One Day International and Twenty20 International status. Wikipedia
      Captains: Rohit Sharma, Hardik Pandya, Suryakumar Yadav, Jasprit Bumrah, KL Rahul, Ruturaj Gaikwad
      Coaches: Rahul Dravid (Head coach), MORE
      Arenas/Stadiums: Wankhede Stadium, Eden Gardens, MORE
      Association: Board of Control for Cricket in India
      First ODI: v England at Headingley, Leeds; 13 July 1974
      First T20I: v South Africa at Wanderers Stadium, Johannesburg; 1 December 2006
